# Game/Replay/AnimatePlaceHand.elm — EARLY

Replay animation driver for PlaceHand — companion to
`AnimateMergeHand`.

A hand card is dragged to an empty spot on the board,
becoming a new single-card stack. Same two-phase async
shape as `AnimateMergeHand`; the only difference is how the
target endpoint is computed — payload's explicit `loc`
field, translated into viewport via the live board rect.

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. Near-twin of `AnimateMergeHand`; see
  that sidecar for the two-phase rationale.

## Interface

```elm
type alias PrepareResult =
    { source : DragSource
    , handCardToMeasure : Card
    }

prepare : { handCard, loc } -> Model -> Maybe PrepareResult

finish :
    { handCard, loc }
    -> Point      -- origin from DOM (hand card top-left)
    -> Float      -- nowMs
    -> DragSource -- from the stashed AwaitingHandRect ctx
    -> Model
    -> Maybe Space.AnimationInfo
```

`finish` returns Nothing only if the live board rect isn't
available; PlaceHand's target doesn't depend on any other
board stack.

## Dependencies

- `Game.Replay.Space` — for `handCardSource`,
  `pointInLiveViewport`, `linearPath`, `AnimationInfo`.
- `Game.CardStack` — for `BoardLocation`.
- `Game.WireAction` — for `WA.PlaceHand`.
- `Main.State` — for `Model`, `DragSource`, `PathFrame`,
  `Point`.

## Pointers

- Called from `Game.Replay.Time.prepareHandAnim` /
  `finishHandAnim`.
- Sibling: `AnimateMergeHand`.
